Best Answer (Recommended) ✅

> “I’ve learned a lot in my Operations Engineer role, especially in system monitoring, incident handling, and infrastructure support. Over time, I realized my long-term career interest is in cybersecurity, specifically Security Operations (SOC). To align my career growth with this goal, I’ve decided to move into a role that allows me to focus more on security monitoring and incident response.”



✔ Honest
✔ Career-growth focused
✔ No negativity about company or manager


---

Short & Simple Version

> “I’m looking to transition my career toward cybersecurity and SOC roles, which aligns better with my long-term professional goals.”




---

If HR Asks: “Why SOC from Operations?”

> “While working in operations, I got exposure to logs, incidents, servers, and security alerts. That exposure sparked my interest in security operations, and I want to build deeper expertise in that area.”




---

If HR Asks: “Is there any issue with the team or manager?”

Never blame anyone. Say:

> “No issues at all. I’ve had a good experience here. This decision is purely based on my long-term career direction.”




---

If HR Asks: “Why now?”

> “I feel this is the right time because I’ve built a strong operational foundation, and transitioning now will help me grow more effectively in cybersecurity.”
